{
  "texts": [
    "The black-box nature of most deep learning models poses a significant barrier to their acceptance, particularly in applications requiring scientific validation, such as health diagnostics or regulatory compliance in the food industry (Nasarian et al. 2024).",
    "Regulatory bodies often demand clear explanations for AIdriven flavor classifications or predictions related to consumer behavior.",
    "To build trust, it is essential to employ explainable AI (XAI) techniques, such as SHAP (Shapley Additive Explanations) or LIME (Local Interpretable Model-Agnostic Explanations).",
    "Future developments should prioritize integrating XAI into sensory research pipelines, allowing researchers, regulators, and consumers to better understand model outputs and their implications.",
    "(4) Experimental Validation and Real-World Verification."
  ]
}